AMENDMENTS TO LB1209
Introduced by Clements, 2.
1 1. Strike the original sections and insert the following new
2 sections:
3 Section 1. DEFINITION OF APPROPRIATION PERIOD.
4 For purposes of this act and any other legislative bill passed by
5 the One Hundred Ninth Legislature, First or Second Session, which
6 appropriates funds, FY2025-26 means the period July 1, 2025, through June
7 30, 2026; FY2026-27 means the period July 1, 2026, through June 30, 2027;
8 FY2027-28 means the period July 1, 2027, through June 30, 2028; and
9 FY2028-29 means the period July 1, 2028, through June 30, 2029.
10 Sec. 2. APPROPRIATION LANGUAGE.
11 There are hereby appropriated, for FY2025-26 and FY2026-27, the sums
12 set forth in this act to each agency for each program from the respective
13 funds for the general operations of state government, postsecondary
14 education, and state aid, except as otherwise appropriated.
15 Sec. 3. UNEXPENDED BALANCES AND CERTIFIED ENCUMBRANCES.
16 All General Fund appropriations existing on June 30, 2025, in excess
17 of expended and certified encumbrance amounts are hereby lapsed unless
18 otherwise provided. All Cash Fund and Revolving Fund appropriations
19 existing on June 30, 2025, in excess of expended and certified
20 encumbrance amounts are hereby lapsed unless otherwise expressly
21 provided. All certified encumbrance amounts on June 30, 2025, and June
22 30, 2026, are hereby reappropriated for FY2025-26 and FY2026-27,
23 respectively, which amounts shall be in addition to the amounts shown in
24 this act.
25 Sec. 4. REAPPROPRIATION OF BALANCE, FY2025-26 to FY2026-27.
26 In addition to the appropriations set forth in this act, there are
27 hereby reappropriated all unexpended appropriation balances existing on
-1-

AM3133 AM3133
LB1209 LB1209
MMM - 04/07/2026 MMM - 04/07/2026
1 June 30, 2026, for FY2026-27, to the respective agencies, programs, and
2 funds listed in this act, except as otherwise provided in this act.
3 Sec. 5. There are hereby reappropriated for each agency, program,
4 and fund for FY2025-26 and FY2026-27, any appropriation by the One
5 Hundred Seventh Legislature, First or Second Session, of the unexpended
6 and unencumbered appropriation balances of the Federal Funds allocated to
7 the State of Nebraska from the federal Coronavirus State Fiscal Recovery
8 Fund pursuant to the federal American Rescue Plan Act of 2021, 42 U.S.C.
9 802, as amended, unless otherwise indicated in this act and any other
10 legislative bill passed by the One Hundred Eighth Legislature, First or
11 Second Session. Such reappropriation shall retain any provided
12 limitations established by the appropriating legislative bill unless
13 otherwise indicated within this act and any other legislative bill passed
14 by the One Hundred Eighth Legislature, First or Second Session.
15 Sec. 6. NEBRASKA ACCOUNTING SYSTEM MANUAL DEFINITIONS.
16 The definitions contained in the Nebraska Accounting System Manual,
17 and any amendments thereto, on file with the Clerk of the Legislature,
18 are hereby adopted by the Legislature as the definitions for this act,
19 except as provided in section 7 of this act.
20 Sec. 7. LIMITATION ON SALARIES, WAGES, AND PER DIEMS.
21 (1) For purposes of this act, (a) SALARY LIMIT shall mean total
22 expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per diems and (b)
23 total expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per diems
24 shall mean all remuneration paid to employees treated as taxable
25 compensation by the Internal Revenue Service or subject to social
26 security coverage, specifically including payments accounted for as
27 vacation, holidays, sick leave, military leave, funeral leave, maternity
28 leave, administrative leave, compensatory time, deferred compensation, or
29 any other similar form, and amounts withheld pursuant to law, but
30 excluding state contributions for social security, retirement, and
31 employee insurance plans.
-2-

AM3133 AM3133
LB1209 LB1209
MMM - 04/07/2026 MMM - 04/07/2026
1 (2) Total expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per
2 diems shall be limited to the amount shown except when federal funds in
3 excess of the amount shown are available and approved by the Governor.
4 Expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per diems from such
5 grants shall be in addition to the limitation on permanent and temporary
6 salaries and per diems otherwise shown in this act. No agency shall
7 request any state funds for continuation or replacement of any such
8 personnel or activities in future budget requests. To the extent
9 feasible, requests for increases in the limitation on permanent and
10 temporary salaries and per diems shall be addressed to the Appropriations
11 Committee of the Legislature when the Legislature is in session.
12 (3) Expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries resulting from
13 awards made to employees under sections 81-1346 to 81-1354 shall be in
14 addition to the limitations on permanent and temporary salaries and per
15 diems otherwise shown in this act.
16 (4) The limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary
17 salaries and per diems for FY2026-27 as enumerated in this act shall be
18 the basis for continuation funding for each fiscal year of the succeeding
19 biennium.
20 (5) The limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary
21 salaries and per diems for FY2025-26 shall be increased by certified
22 encumbrance amounts from FY2024-25 for permanent and temporary salaries
23 and per diems. The limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary
24 salaries and per diems for FY2026-27 shall be increased by certified
25 encumbrance amounts from FY2025-26 for permanent and temporary salaries
26 and per diems. Encumbered amounts shall be calculated in accordance with
27 section 81-138.01.
28 (6) The limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary
29 salaries and per diems shall only apply to remuneration paid to state
30 employees or per diem payments made to members of state boards or
31 commissions.
