1 (7) The budget administrator of the budget division of the
2 Department of Administrative Services may administratively increase the
3 limitation on expenditures for permanent and temporary salaries and per
4 diems upon receipt of a request for such increase from the director of a
5 state agency certifying the actual amount of the payment to a former
6 employee of such agency, or such employee's beneficiary upon the death of
7 the employee, of accumulated vacation and sick leave pursuant to section
8 81-1325 and the rules and regulations of the State Personnel System
9 governing such payments.
10 Sec. 8. DRAWING AND PAYING WARRANTS.
11 The Director of Administrative Services shall draw warrants upon the
12 proper fund in the state treasury for an amount not to exceed the
13 appropriations set forth in this act upon presentation of proper
14 documentation. The State Treasurer shall pay the warrants out of the
15 appropriate funds.
